OL,3,CVeteran rowing across Atlantic to
OL,4,CBarbados for charity
OL,6,FA veteran from Plymouth who has
OL,7,Fbattled with PTSD and homelessness is
OL,8,Fnearing the end of his epic challenge
OL,9,F- rowing across the Atlantic.
OL,11,FFormer Royal Marines Commando Chris
OL,12,FThrall is expected to complete his
OL,13,F3,000-mile journey crossing from Gran
OL,14,FCanaria to Barbados later this month.
OL,16,FThe 54-year-old has been joined by
OL,17,Ffellow veteran and first mate Louie
OL,18,FGreenhalgh as the pair raise money for
OL,19,Fcharity.
