OL,3,CVeteran rowing across Atlantic to
OL,4,CBarbados for charity
OL,6,F"Hang on in there and hopefully, you
OL,7,Fcan take an example from us because
OL,8,Fwe're having the adventure of a
OL,9,Flifetime - rowing to Barbados from
OL,10,FGran Canaria.
OL,12,F"It's 3,000 miles! We're out here on
OL,13,Four own. If we're not out here rowing,
OL,14,Fwe're having a nap in the cabin or I'm
OL,15,Ftrying to do some social media."
OL,17,FChris, who now works as a motivational
OL,18,Fspeaker and mindset coach, said he
OL,19,Fwants to "keep the spirit of adventure
OL,20,Falive and inspire the younger
OL,21,Fgeneration".
